---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../consts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header title={SITE_TITLE} />
    <main>
      <h1>Hello fellow coder!</h1>
      <p>
        Life as a software engineer is a mix of creativity, problem-solving, and
        collaboration. It's about taking abstract ideas and turning them into
        concrete solutions that people can use. It's about constantly learning
        and adapting to new technologies and trends. And it's about working with
        a team of talented people to build something amazing together.
      </p>
      <p>
        <img style="width:100%"
          src="https://res.cloudinary.com/highereducation/images/f_auto,q_auto/g_face,c_fill,fl_lossy,q_auto:best,w_448,h_382/v1662131318/ComputerScience.org/GettyImages-1180183927_73387d16/GettyImages-1180183927_73387d16.jpg?_i=AA"
        />
      </p>
      <p>
        It's not always easy, of course. There are deadlines to meet, bugs to
        fix, and challenges to overcome. But when you see something you've built
        being used by millions of people, it's a feeling that's hard to beat.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
